---
description: JSDoc comment conventions for TypeScript types and interfaces
globs: **/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# JSDoc on All Type Properties

Every property in an `interface`, `type`, or inline object type **must** have a `/** ... */` JSDoc comment. This includes function parameter object types, generic type arguments, and return types.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — missing comments
export interface FooInput {
  id: string;
  title?: string;
  tags?: string[];
}

// ✅ GOOD
export interface FooInput {
  /** Unique identifier */
  id: string;
  /** Display title */
  title?: string;
  /** Associated tags */
  tags?: string[];
}
```

# No Inline JSDoc in Object Types

Never place `/** ... */` JSDoc comments inline on the same line as the property. Always expand to multi-line.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
options: { /** Logger instance */ logger: Logger }
nodes: { /** Token */ token: string }[]

// ✅ GOOD
options: {
  /** Logger instance */
  logger: Logger;
}
nodes: {
  /** Token */
  token: string;
}[]
```

This applies to inline types in function parameters, interface properties, and generic type arguments alike.
